Try adding the `ng-model-options=&quot;{ allowInvalid: true }&quot;` attribute to your input field. This will help you get the value typed in the field. You can read more about it [here](https://www.w3schools.com/angular/ng_ng-model-options.asp).

As for your first problem, get your isValidSwedishSSN to return true in case of valid input and false in case of invalid input. This value will be set in `ng-pattern`. Then in the form&#39;s `ng-submit`, check if the form is valid and then submit.
```
&lt;form name=&#39;testFrom&#39; ng-submit=&#39;testForm.$valid &amp;&amp; submitFunc()&#39;&gt;
    &lt;!-- form input fields --&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
```
The form will not be submitted in case ng-pattern is false.

