There isn&#39;t any accurate method to calculate the size of a managed object, but you can get a rough estimate using [GC.GetTotalMemory](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.gc.gettotalmemory?view=netframework-4.8).

Something like this:


    long start = GC.GetTotalMemory(true);
    
    var values = new object[data.Length];
    // add row values to values 
    dataTable.Rows.Add(values);
    
    long used = GC.GetTotalMemory(true) - start;

`used` will be your used memory.

